         <div type="translation">
            <p>
               <supplied reason="lost">The Council</supplied>
               <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">and the People</supplied> and the Gerousia honoured <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">with the erection</supplied> of statues Tib<ex>erius</ex> Cl<ex>audius</ex> Ktesias <gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/>
               <supplied reason="lost">and</supplied>
               <name>
                  <gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/>ia</name> his wife and <supplied reason="lost">Tib<ex>erius</ex> Cl<ex>audius</ex>
               </supplied>  their son, on account of their lives <supplied reason="lost">of</supplied>
               <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">virtue and</supplied> dignity, since they dedicated for <supplied reason="lost">perpetual</supplied> distributions and crownings both to the Council <supplied reason="lost">and</supplied> to the Tribes and <seg cert="low">those who drew lots first</seg> [? the annual interest] on 11,000 denarii.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Waddington restored <foreign xml:lang="grc">
                  <supplied reason="lost">ἡ βουλὴ καὶ</supplied> ἡ γερουσία</foreign> in the first line, consequently shortening the supplement required on the left.</p>
